{"word":"διάβολος","slug":"διάβολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>διάβολος, ον</el></b> [<el>δια, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βάλλω\">βάλλω</a></el>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:διαβάλλω\">διαβάλλω</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ adj.\">adj.</a> <b><i>slanderous</i> <a href='B:610 3:11'>1 Ti 3:11</a>; <a href='B:620 3:3'>2 Ti 3:3</a>; <a href='B:630 2:3'>Tit 2:3</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> as noun, <b><i>slanderer, adversary,</i></b> except for <a href='B:500 6:70'>J 6:70</a>, always as title of the transcendent exemplar of evil<i>the Devil</i> <b><a href='B:470 4:1'>Mt 4:1</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; kinship imagery <b><a href='B:500 8:44'>J 8:44</a>; <a href='B:510 13:10'>Ac 13:10</a>; <a href='B:690 3:8'>1 J 3:8</a>, <a href='B:690 3:10'>10</a>.</b> —Transferred sense, of Judas <b><a href='B:500 6:70'>J 6:70</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:διαβλέπω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:διαγγέλλω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}